Google: 3.5'' external hard drive enclosure TWO MAIN SIZES OF HD: 3.5'' = desktop HD 2.5'' = notebook HD External enclosrues are made for both sizes.
There are models available that will enclose an IDE (PATA) or SATA HD.
Your local computer and electronics stores carry them.
Cheapest prices are usually found online.
Adapters without a case are available as a nice temporary solution.
Example: http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.asp?Item=N82E16812156101 NOTE: Connecting an external HD to a Windows XP machine via USB 2.0 has a better track record than Firewire.
There are also some models that connect to an external SATA port.
